@NODE BENCHMARK
  HypAss benchmarks

  I frequently optimize all routines, since I started the speed of HypAss
  increased about 500%.... (to be continued)
  Here are some examples to show that HypAss is neither the fastest nor the
  slowest assembler of the world:

  The first example is taken out the "WD65C816 S-NES Macro Assembler v1.4
  [MC68030], © 1993 by Infernal Byte, INC" example sources and contains
  405111 lines with rts each line:

    Source:  ram:rts.s (2025555 bytes)
      Code:             0 -> 62E74    =    405108 bytes
      Source:     2025555    Syntax:    XASS    Includes:     1
      Lines:       405112    Math:       HYP    Labels:       1 of 200
      Passes:           2    Cpu:       6502    Symbols:      2 of 200
      Memory:     2705336    Object:     CBM    Macros:       0
      Time:       07:36.4    Dummies:      0    FwrdRefs:     0

      This "speed" will increase by 100% when HypAss will have its
      multi-pass features. Then this will be solved in 1 pass. (now: 2)

        888  lines/s
        4442 bytes/s

      The horribly fast S-NES assembler just needs 22 seconds!


  This example contains 9271 lines real source code:

    Source:   hsrc:old/-JOIN.hsrc
      Code:             0 -> 2C42     =     11330 bytes
      Source:      219674    Syntax:    XASS    Includes:     1
      Lines:         9271    Math:       HYP    Labels:     705 of 2000
      Passes:           2    Cpu:       6502    Symbols:    498 of 2000
      Memory:      631968    Object:     CBM    Macros:      20
      Time:       00:16.5    Dummies:      0    FwrdRefs:   414
    No errors.

         561 lines/s
       13313 bytes/s

    When tested with buffalo32 source (about 130K), HypAss had 2 times
    the speed of AS11 from the motorola freeware assemblers.

    When tested with a 225K source in 47 includes, HypAss had 2.86 times
    the speed of XAss64 1.0.

